I think by now everyone is pretty much bored to death and sick of eharing 
about your supposed IQ of 150. Quite frankly I wouldn't care if it was 250, 
50, a 40, 88mm, or just plain 1. The fact of the matter is, intelligence is 
not something to gloat about which is something I bet you do in school alot 
and is the reason why you get made of fun so much. 

~LN

P.S. If you learned what I did from watching bedazzled, you'd know that 
overly intelligent people ARE gay. Let's see how often you brag about your 
intelligence now.

In a message dated 9/17/02 7:44:32 AM Eastern Daylight Time, 
dewboy30816@... writes:


> And I have an IQ of 150. 
> Please don't shove it down my throat if yours is
> higher, I'm just telling you I'm not an idiot.  And
> while I sometimes sound rude I said that simply
> pointing out "long live" is the general expression. 
> Actually "long life" may be nice for a change, but
> "long live so-and-so is all I've ever heard said.  I'm
> not taking a shot at airly, if I made a mistake like
> that in Spanish I'd want him to tell me.
> 



--part1_15e.13f8b06e.2ab87bfb_boundary
